        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Philad.</placeName>
                <date>July 29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5620</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Miss Rosa Mordecai</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Watervliet Arsenal NB.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>My dear Friend.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your very refreshing note was received<lb/> about an hour ago, and I
                assure you that it almost compliments<lb/> me for so much suffering as I had been
                sure,<lb/> to have so many kind inquiries made by my<lb/> friends, you &amp; yours
                included. I today sat up for<lb/> the first time to write at a table since my<lb/>
                last yesterday two weeks <add>?</add> and I trust that<lb/> by middle of next week I
                shall be <add>?</add><lb/> more to be out. But I am admonished by the<lb/>
                <add>?</add>tant pain whenever <add>?</add>, that it will<lb/> be a long while
                before I shall be exempt from<lb/> the consequences of an accident as painful
                as<lb/> unlooked for. <persName>Jones I Horace</persName>
                <add>?</add> last evening,<lb/> in my bed <add>?</add>. I am indebted to him for his
                constant<lb/> inquiries.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The house is emptied of all its inhabitants<lb/> some of servants;
                and how pleased would I<lb/> be to have you here for an uninterrupted quarrel</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>on any given topic for though my back is<lb/> lamed, my tongue is loose on the proper
                    <add>?</add>.<lb/> Only ladies have the privilege of a tongue<lb/> fastening in
                the middle; we from miserable<lb/> masculiness must needs be <add>?</add> well
                the<lb/> use of it in the front part. But then we may<lb/> not try it then to the
                best advantage, even<lb/>
                <add>?</add> arguing the ladies.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My writing is hardly presu<add>?</add> to a<lb/> lady; than to
                    <add>?</add> almost straight up to make<lb/>
                <add>?</add>, and being near sighted with all,<lb/> to not writing with spectacles,
                than to trust<lb/> to my readiness in handling the pen to make<lb/> it figures as
                they come without having any hope<lb/> of offering a specimen of caligraphy.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Remember me to your parents and <add>?</add>,<lb/> &amp; return to
                bless <add>?</add> my best thanks for<lb/> he<add>?</add> joint kind inquiries.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Hoping that the course of your life<lb/> may run smooth without
                accident or<lb/> severe trials I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">truly your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName>
            </p>
